content.text:
Both use the **OpenAI-compatible** format — same structure, different base URLs.

**OpenRouter** (`https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions`):
```json
// Request
{
  "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4",
  "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "..."}],
  "stream": true,
  "max_tokens": 1024
}

// Response
{
  "id": "gen-...",
  "choices": [{"message": {"role": "assistant", "content": "..."}, "finish_reason": "stop"}],
  "usage": {"prompt_tokens": 10, "completion_tokens": 20, "total_tokens": 30}
}

// Streaming: data: {"choices":[{"delta":{"content":"..."}}]}
```

**Ollama** (`http://localhost:11434/v1/chat/completions`):
Same OpenAI-compatible format since Ollama added the `/v1/` compatibility layer. Also has its native API at `/api/chat` with a slightly different shape but the `/v1/` path is what most tools use.

**The key difference from Anthropic:**

| | Anthropic `/v1/messages` | OpenAI `/v1/chat/completions` |
|---|---|---|
| System prompt | Separate `system` field | `{"role": "system"}` in messages |
| Response | `content: [{type: "text", text: "..."}]` | `choices[0].message.content: "..."` |
| Tool use | `content` blocks with `type: "tool_use"` | `tool_calls` array on message |
| Streaming events | Typed SSE (`content_block_delta`, `message_delta`) | Single `choices[0].delta` shape |
| Auth | `x-api-key` header | `Authorization: Bearer` header |
| Usage in stream | Split across `message_start` + `message_delta` | In final `[DONE]`-preceding chunk |

So for `proxy/llm/openrouter` and `proxy/llm/ollama`, the proxy logic would be structurally the same (both OpenAI format) — just different upstream URLs and auth handling. The Anthropic proxy is the odd one out with its unique format.

